\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. P. alpigena} (Fries) Lindman, {\i Svensk Fanerogamfl.} 91 (1918) ({\i P. pratensis} subsp.{\i  alpigena} (Fries) Hiit.). Plant 20-30(-50) cm, with long rhizomes, not forming compact tussocks; non-flowering shoots distichously leafy. Leaves 2-3(-4) mm wide, abruptly contracted into a cucullate apex. Panicle 6-8 cm, compact, ovoid to pyramidal, the lower branches usually in pairs. Spikelets with 3-5 florets, sometimes proliferating; keels of the palea ciliate below. 2n = 35, 43, 56, 70-72, 84.{\i  Heaths and pastures. N. Europe, southwards to S. Norway}. Fa Fe Is No Rs (N, C) Sb Su.
\par

