\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. P. pratensis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 67 (1753) (incl.{\i  P. pinegensis} Roshev., {\i P. turfosa} Litv.). Bright green, rather laxly caespitose; stems (15-)20-50(-70) cm. Leaves 2-3 mm wide, flat or canaliculate, shorter than the stem. Ligule c. 1 mm, decurrent on sheath-margins. Panicle 6-15 cm, the lower branches mostly 3-5 together. Glumes unequal, acute, the lower 1-veined. 2n = 42, 50-78, 91, 98. {\i Throughout Europe.} All except Bl; introduced in Az.
